					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-995675#post-2276964</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-995675/scp-2703#post-2276964</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Thu, 23 Apr 2015 17:53:05 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>Rioghail</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>1302192</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>This is pretty much just weirdness for weirdness' sake. I didn't see anything that didn't seem calculated to produce a particular brand of 'quirky' weirdness that lacks narrative substance. It seems like an inferior version of <a href="http://www.scpwiki.com/scp-1972">SCP-1972</a> that isn't willing to go in the direction that 1972 went, but also lacks any of the characterisation or humour that makes it effective.</p> <p>That, and the bizarre bit about how this thing 'just got depressed' when the word being looked for is 'upset,' or, less charitably, 'sulking' didn't win it any favours with me, either.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
