					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-995675#post-2104582</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-995675/scp-2703#post-2104582</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Sun, 07 Sep 2014 20:13:00 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>VAElynx</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>914331</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>While this isn't bad, and the extradimensional entity's accidental use of a phrase with very, very different connotations to what it intended is amusing, ultimately, the article leaves me unimpressed as far too much &quot;weird for the sake of weird&quot; type of thing.</p> <p>Neutral vote.</p> <p>BTW am I right that it's another of those things that feed on the subject's emotions? The test logs as well as its pursuit of satisfying its &quot;clients&quot; makes me suspect it to be the case.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
